default&#xa0;
default4.3
default&#xa0; 
defaultIn its report into Building Regulations applying to electrical and gas installation and repairs in dwellings (March 2012), the Committee described the “stringent criteria” which must be met by organisations wishing to establish a Competent Persons Scheme. 
defaultThose organisations must set an appropriately high standard of competence for members, and commit to testing members to that standard. 
default&#xa0;
default4.4
default&#xa0; 
defaultIn turn, prospective electrical contractors must undertake an accreditation process in order to become members of 
defaulta
default Com
defaultpetent Persons Scheme.
default Contractors must complete a minimum of 224 guided learning hours in order to gain the qualifications necessary to 
defaultbe considered for accreditation
default.
default&#xa0;
default4.5
default&#xa0; 
defaultA further advantage to the current system is the focus on 
defaultimproving 
defaultstandards year-on-year. 
defaultWe are pleased that 
defaultthe Minimal Technical Competence (MTC) to apply for Part P certification has been gradually raised since the introduction of the regulations in 2005. As of April 2013, those 
defaultwishing to register with a Scheme must
default demonstrate competence equivalent to a Level 3 qualification.
default 
default&#xa0;
default4.6
default&#xa0; 
defaultNor is accreditation guaranteed. The average first time pass rate of the accreditation process is 81.4%.
default&#xa0;
default4.7
default&#xa0; 
defaultOnce qualified, electrical contractors are subject to regular assessment as members o
defaultf the Competent
default Persons Scheme. Contractors are inspected at least once a year by an appointed supervisor
default w
defaultho records
default a range of 
defaultindicators
default,
default including the quality of their workmanship and the state of their equipment
default.
default&#xa0;
default4.8
default&#xa0; 
defaultThe 
defaultSelect Committee’s original 
defaultreport concluded that 
defaultan “expected benefit” of 
defaultthis system of stringent accreditation and regular assessment had 
defaultwould be
default higher quality workmanship, and a fall in the number of installations by poorly qualified contractors
default.
default&#xa0;
default4.9
default&#xa0; 
defaultT
defaulthe process of assessment 
defaultis
default 
defaultunder constant review
default, with improvements made as necessary
default. 
defaultFor example, a
defaults a result of the Part P Impact Assessment
default,
default the principle of “risk-based inspection” has been introduced
default.
default 
default This means
default, for example,
default that members with poor customer complaints records can be inspected more often, and those with exemplary records less.  
