default6.1
default&#xa0; 
defaultIn light of the Committee’s on
default-
defaultgoing inquiry focused on the building 
defaultregulations, t
defaulthe ESC 
defaultwould like to raise its concern regarding proposals for 
defaultthird party inspection and testing
default. 
defaultWe believe that
default, by allowing professional electricians the opportunity to sign off the work 
defaultof their peers, the new scheme undermines the self-
defaultcertification principle of Part P and thus could lead to significant numbers of electricians de
default-
defaultregistering in favour of having their work signed off by others. If this scheme does lead to mass deregistration, it would also mean a fall-back in the number o
defaultf electricians being inspected and tested every year 
defaultand resultant safety implications.
default&#xa0;
default6.2
default&#xa0; 
defaultIn order to avoid the outcome above, we
default 
defaultrecommend that third party inspections exclude work carried out by means of trade
default. This mirrors requirements for gas 
defaultinstallations and would, in our view, mean that the system does not have the unintended consequence of encouraging electricians to renege on their C
defaultompetent 
defaultP
defaulterson 
defaultS
defaultcheme
default membership. 
